## Skill Category Taxonomy

Functional classification based on Thariq Shihipar's 9-category framework (Anthropic Claude Code team). Use this taxonomy for coverage gap analysis and new skill creation guidance. Some skills span multiple categories.

| Category | Description | Project Examples |
|----------|-------------|-----------------|
| Library/API Reference | Explain how to use libraries, CLIs, SDKs correctly | `anthropic-claude-api`, `anthropic-mcp-builder`, `hf-cli`, `tossinvest-cli`, `gws-*`, `context7-mcp` |
| Product Verification | Test or verify that code works (often paired with browser/tmux tools) | `e2e-testing`, `qa-dogfood`, `expect-qa`, `anthropic-webapp-testing`, `canary-monitor`, `e2e-overhaul` |
| Data Fetching & Analysis | Connect to data and monitoring stacks | `alphaear-stock`, `alphaear-news`, `hf-dataset-viewer`, `tab-*`, `weekly-stock-update`, `daily-stock-check` |
| Business Process & Team Automation | Automate repetitive workflows into one command | `standup-digest`, `commit-to-issue`, `meeting-digest`, `google-daily`, `eod-ship`, `sod-ship` |
| Code Scaffolding & Templates | Generate framework boilerplate | `fsd-development`, `create-skill`, `anthropic-skill-creator`, `office-template-enforcer`, `fe-pipeline` |
| Code Quality & Review | Enforce quality standards and review code | `deep-review`, `simplify`, `omc-ai-slop-cleaner`, `code-review-all`, `test-suite`, `security-expert` |
| CI/CD & Deployment | Fetch, push, deploy code | `ci-quality-gate`, `release-commander`, `ship`, `release-ship`, `domain-commit` |
| Runbooks | Map symptoms to multi-tool investigation procedures | `diagnose`, `incident-to-improvement`, `service-health-doctor`, `infra-runbook-generator` |
| Infrastructure Operations | Routine maintenance with guardrails for destructive actions | `dependency-auditor`, `infra-drift-detector`, `compliance-gate`, `slack-orphan-cleaner`, `helm-validator` |

## Orchestration Rules

- For multi-skill tasks, read `mission-control` SKILL.md first
- Always read a skill's SKILL.md before delegating to it
- Track orchestration progress in `tasks/todo.md`
- Record failures and lessons in `tasks/lessons.md`
